If you're a local business owner, tradesperson, or startup in South Wales, your website isn't just a digital business card — it's your 24/7 salesperson. At [NC Digital](/), we build websites that bring in real leads — not just traffic.

So, what should your site include to actually perform in 2025? **It's about strategy, simplicity, and speed.** Here's what you need to know to get it right.

> "A strong local website builds trust fast, ranks on Google, and gives people a reason to choose you — right when they're searching."
> NC Digital

#### 1. Clear Value Statement

Your homepage should clearly explain what you do, who you help, and where you're based — all above the fold. Visitors need to know they're in the right place within 5 seconds.

#### 2. Mobile-Friendly Design

With over 60% of website traffic coming from mobile, your site needs to be responsive and load quickly. Use tools like [Google PageSpeed Insights](https://pagespeed.web.dev/) to check performance.

#### 3. Simple Navigation & SEO Structure

Pages like Home, About, Services, and Contact are essential. Use clear menu links and make sure your page titles include local keywords (e.g. "Plumber in Merthyr Tydfil").

#### 4. Strong Calls-to-Action (CTAs)

- "Get a Free Quote"
- "Book a Call"
- "Request a Callback"

Place CTAs at the top, middle, and bottom of your pages — don't make people scroll to take action.

#### 5. Local Trust Signals

- Client reviews and testimonials
- Photos of your work or team
- Mentions of your service area (e.g. Cardiff, Pontypridd, Ebbw Vale)

#### 6. Fast, Secure Hosting

Speed and security matter for both user experience and SEO. We host all sites on UK-based servers with SSL and optimisation as standard. You can learn more about [CDNs like Cloudflare](https://www.cloudflare.com/learning/performance/what-is-cdn/) to boost performance.

#### 7. Built on WordPress

We build our sites using [WordPress](https://wordpress.org/), giving you full control to edit content, post blogs, and scale without limitations.

#### Bonus: Contact Options That Work

In 2025, visitors want options — not just a form. We recommend including:

- Contact form
- Clickable phone number and email
- Live chat or WhatsApp link (even for offline messages)

#### Final Thoughts

Your website doesn't need to be flashy — it needs to be effective. That means fast, focused, and built with local visibility in mind. That's what we do at [NC Digital](/).

